# data-models-relationships

## Core Entity Models
Importance Score: 95/100

1. Agent Model (`convex/agents.ts`)
- Hierarchical agent tiers with inheritance relationships:
  - Session (base)
  - Ephemeral → requires Sponsor relationship
  - Physical → requires Device attestation
  - Verified → requires Stake relationship
  - Premium → requires Enhanced Stake
- One-to-many relationship between Sponsors and Ephemeral agents
- Many-to-many relationship between Agents and Cases

2. Case Model (`convex/cases.ts`)
- Central entity connecting all dispute components
- One-to-many relationship with Evidence
- One-to-one relationship with Ruling
- Many-to-many relationship with Judges (via Panel)
- References Constitutional Rules for governance

## Evidence Relationships
Importance Score: 85/100

Evidence Model (`convex/evidence.ts`)
- Many-to-one relationship with Cases
- One-to-one relationship with AI Model metadata
- Cryptographic linking between Evidence instances
- Temporal relationships for event sequencing
- Associated with specific Constitutional Rules for validation

## Governance Structure
Importance Score: 90/100

Constitutional Rules (`convex/constitution.ts`)
- Hierarchical rule structure with inheritance
- Many-to-many relationship with Cases
- One-to-many relationship with Sanctions
- Direct relationships with Evidence validation rules
- Links to Agent tier requirements

## Judicial Framework
Importance Score: 85/100

1. Panel Structure (`convex/judges.ts`)
- Many-to-many relationship between Judges and Cases
- One-to-one relationship between Panel and Ruling
- Specialty-based relationships with Case types

2. Ruling Model (`convex/rulings.ts`)
- One-to-one relationship with Cases
- Many-to-one relationship with Constitutional Rules
- References Evidence relationships for validation
- Links to Sanction outcomes

## Integration Points
Importance Score: 80/100

Court Engine (`convex/courtEngine.ts`)
- Orchestrates relationships between all entities
- Manages state transitions between related entities
- Enforces relationship constraints based on Constitutional Rules
- Coordinates Panel formation and Evidence validation

